All Classes

Class Summary
Class
Description
DatabaseManager
This class talks to the database and returns the data if required.
FileManager
This class talks to the overpass API, and processes the data so its can be used by the pathfinding algorithm.
FileManagerTests
Test class which tests data.FileManager.
LoadingDialog
loading dialogs are created when the application starts the pathfinder, to show the progress of the application.
MetInserter
This class is used to make it easier to insert MetValues into the database.
MetValue
Data class for met values.
MetValueTests
Test class for the toString method of the MetValues class.
Node
A node is a location point tied to an id, multiple nodes make up a way.
NodeTests
Test class for algorithm.Node class.
OutputScreen
The output screen which shows the data of the path when the algorithm is done.
PathFinder
This class generates a path of a given length, or null if a path cannot be found.
PathfinderTests
Test class for the algorithm.PathFinder class.
PathFindingActivity
This class fetches the data for the pathfinding algorithm and passes it to the pathfinding algorithm, and shows the progress.
PathNotFound
This is created when a path cannot be found.
User
A data class for the user, stores the data entered by the user and calculates the distance required of the path.
UserInputScreen
The main screen, the user enters the input, and when the button is pressed the input is validated.
UserTests
Test class for the data.User class.
Way
A way contains two or more nodes, linked together by a number.
WayTests
Test class for the algorithm.Way class.
WayType
Data class for types of way, used in building queries for overpass.
